intro : "<p>Delusion, according to Oxford dictionary, means a false belief or judgment about external reality, held despite incontrovertible evidence to the contrary. Within Japanese media fandom, we fellow weebs have been (over)exposed to one kind of delusion over and over; Chunibyou. The delusion of grandeur often exhibited by middle schooler, with the name literally meaning 'Middle School Second Year syndrome', or 'Eight-Grader Syndrome'.</p>

<p>We see chuunibyou becoming the most powerful being in the universe (Eminence in Shadow, Fire Force), we see chuunibyou in games, spouting cryptic stuff that goes against the lore of that game universe (Fischl from Genshin, Guillotine from NIKKE, Rappa from HSR).</p>

<p>But when does this term starts to get known by people in the first place?</p>

<p><i>Chuunibyou demo Koi ga Shitai!</i> was released back in October 2012, and coincidentally, the google search around that time regarding the word 'Chuunibyou' rose exponentially. It is not hyperbole to say that this series is responsible for bringing the term to the forefront, and it was my absolute pleasure to be contracted this series for the Fall 2024 season.</p>"
