<p>Chuunibyou is one of the series I've been wanting to watch for a while now. Images of Rikka have floated around on the internet, and her pained voicelines is something I used when I was in VC with my peers, added by someone who clearly loves the series.</p>

<p>Coming in, I did not expect the MC, Yuuta, to be a <i>former</i> Chuuni. I was under the impression for years that he is a normal guy that got entangled with the clearly Chuunibyou-addled mind that is Takanashi Rikka, but apparently it's not that simple...</p>

<p>Having him as a mc being embarassed of his Chuuni days... made me remember my own chuuni phase that starts in HIGH SCHOOL, UNLIKE HIM WHO STOPPED AT HIGH SCHOOL.</p>

<p>And now I want to roll like him and Nibutani on the floor. Oh yeah, speaking of... we also get the roster of characters that makes up the Magic Society of Napping- okay no I don't really even know what the name of the club is supposed to be. Anime shows and their weird club/circle man...</p>

<p>When I finished the first season... I was emotional. The journey to reach that point has been rife with comedy, but also dramatic rendition of chuuni-ism... but also real story about how people cope using unbelievable situation. Here's my unfiltered (maybe a bit chuuni-ish) paragraph of messages that I wrote at the time, which I believe represent my feeling regarding the first season as a whole, if not the last few episode.</p>